s Limited","website":"https://skycorp.in","city":"Mumbai","full_time_employees":83,"trailing_pe":10.184972,"price_to_book":1.1788121,"book_value":59.789,"eps_trailing":6.92,"dividend_rate":1.0,"dividend_yield":1.42,"payout_ratio":0.1445,"five_yr_avg_div_yield":1.16,"revenue":845016000.0,"revenue_per_share":107.127,"revenue_growth":0.042,"ebitda":96241000.0,"ebitda_margins":0.11389,"gross_margins":0.38901,"operating_margins":0.11241,"profit_margins":0.06455,"net_income":54550000.0,"total_cash":27513000.0,"total_cash_per_share":3.491,"total_debt":138048992.0,"debt_to_equity":29.229,"enterprise_value":666029632.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":6.92,"enterprise_to_revenue":0.788,"earnings_growth":0.143,"shares_outstanding":7890541.0,"float_shares":1840178.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.73605,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":0.055,"fifty_two_week_high":123.0,"fifty_two_week_low":67.5,"fifty_day_average":84.5448,"two_hundred_day_avg":92.33805,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":173.5,"all_time_low":73.15,"long_business_summary":"Sky Industries Limited manufactures, markets, and sells narrow woven fabrics in India. The company offers hook and loop; rubber based, coins, piece cuts, mated piece cuts, and score cuts adhesive; and specialty products, such as molded/injection hook, knit loop/velour, back to back tapes, elasticated loop tapes, bobbin tapes, and auto loop products. It also provides headgears for orthopedic and medical industries; tile grip; jacket cuff, wheelchair sleeve, chaffe, and alligator clip; reinforcement strap, dual loop strap, buckle strap, eyestrap, mobility strap, webbing strap; aplix products; and other products, including webbing, neoprene, insect screen, specialty elastics, velvet tapes, tourniqeuts, and straps. The company serves footwear, orthopedic, defense, medical equipment, automotive, sports, personal protective equipment, packaging, apparel, infant wear, cable networking, FIBC, aviation, home furnishing, luggage, abrasive, stationery, display, warehousing, spinning mills, construction, equestrian, and industrial applications. It also exports its products to the United States, the United Kingdom, Canada, Italy, Germany, Turkey, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, and others. The company was formerly known as Fine Velvets and Plastofabs Private Limited. Sky Industries Limited was incorporated in 1989 and is based in Mumbai, India."}}